Disconnect a Salesforce CRM Connection

You can delete a connection to your Salesforce CRM instance if you don’t need it. Removing the connection stops Data Cloud from using your Salesforce CRM org as a data source and data action target.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
In Data Cloud, select  then  Audience Setup.
In configuration, select Salesforce CRM.
Find the connector you want to disconnect.
Click▼next to the connection name and select Disconnect.
NOTE If the connection you’re trying to disconnect has data streams and associated data action targets, Data Cloud can’t disconnect the connection. To do so, first delete the data streams.
If the connection has no data streams and associated data action targets, click Disconnect to confirm. The instance and all of its data is removed from Data Cloud, but not the trust files.
The instance doesn’t appear in the list of connected Salesforce CRM instances.
NOTE The instance disconnection action can’t be undone.
